  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6598 sitting just below the massive +10.7B gamma wall at 6605 and well below the 6617 flip strike, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that resistance cluster. The PIN regime combined with the concentrated positive gamma between 6600-6610 creates a strong mean-reverting environment that should cap upside momentum. The gex_surge event and extreme short-term percentage changes suggest we're seeing rapid options positioning shifts, but the current setup favors range-bound action with dealers providing liquidity against directional moves.\n\nKey levels: Watch for selling pressure into 6605-6610, while any break below 6500 flips dealers into amplifying mode where they'd accelerate downside moves.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get pinned around current levels with resistance at 6605.",
